#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "UI Overview"
msgstr ""

#. type: TIP
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:35
msgid ""
"❶ Title bar:: Shows the name of this factory controller. Name can be edited "
"by clicking on it."
msgstr ""

#. type: TIP
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:38
msgid "❷ Help button:: Opens this help page."
msgstr ""

#. type: TIP
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:41
msgid ""
"❸ Network selector:: All networks tuned to by components placed in this "
"controller are listed here. Scroll to select a network to highlight its "
"components. While holding a gauge, scroll to tune the gauge to a network. "
"<<Network Selector,More Info>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TIP
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"❹ Capacity indicator:: Shows the maximum number of components that may be placed in this factory controller, as well as how much of this capacity has been taken up.\n"
"The capacity may be modified by the \"Controller Capacity\" server setting."
msgstr ""

#. type: TIP
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:48
msgid "❺ Zoom indicator:: Shows the current zoom level."
msgstr ""

#. type: TIP
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:51
msgid "❻ Settings button:: Opens the settings screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: TIP
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:54
msgid ""
"❼ Player inventory:: Shows the player inventory. Only the 9 hotbar slots are "
"shown by default. Click the \"+\" button to expand the other 27 slots."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Navigation"
msgstr ""

#. type: #navigation
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:59
msgid ""
"Drag with the left mouse button to pan the view around the virtual board. "
"The W, A, S, D keys can also be used to move the view in cardinal directions."
msgstr ""

#. type: #navigation
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:61
msgid "Scroll with the mouse wheel to zoom in/out."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working with Components"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Holding a tuned factory gauge over an empty location"
msgstr ""

#. type: #components
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:69
msgid ""
"To place a component, grab a corresponding item from the inventory and click "
"on an empty spot on the board. The xref:components.adoc[Components] page "
"lists all items that may be placed. Notably, factory gauges need to be "
"<<network-selector,tuned to a network>> before being placed. Placed items "
"will be stored inside the factory controller, even when the factory "
"controller block is mined."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "A just-placed factory gauge"
msgstr ""

#. type: #components
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:74
msgid ""
"Holding shift and clicking on a component removes it from the controller and "
"returns the item to your inventory."
msgstr ""

#. type: #components
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:76
msgid ""
"Either left- or right-clicking a component opens its configuration screen. "
"To move a component, open its screen and click the image:btn-"
"relocate.png[,18,18] \"relocate\" button, then click on a new location for "
"the component."
msgstr ""

#. type: #components
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:78
msgid ""
"Multiple components may be selected. Hold Ctrl and drag with the left mouse "
"button to select all components within a rectangular area. Selected "
"components are indicated with a green outline. To add and remove individual "
"components from the selection, hold Ctrl and left-click them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rectangle-selecting multiple components"
msgstr ""

#. type: #components
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:83
msgid ""
"When components are selected, drag on any of them to move all selected "
"components. Likewise, shift-clicking on any of them removes all selected "
"components from the board."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating and Modifying Connections"
msgstr ""

#. type: #connections
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:88
msgid ""
"Components may be connected to one another. Refer to a specific component's "
"documentation for the functionality provided by connections."
msgstr ""

#. type: #connections
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:90
msgid ""
"To connect component A to B, click on B to open its UI, click on the "
"image:btn-add-connection.png[,18,18] \"add connection\" button, and then "
"click A. Some components may only act as the source or sink of a connection, "
"in which case a valid direction is automatically chosen."
msgstr ""

#. type: #connections
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:92
msgid ""
"A component's UI may allow you to remove its connections. They can also be "
"removed using the dashboard by hovering over them and shift-clicking. When "
"multiple connections overlap, hold shift and scroll while hovering over a "
"spot with overlapping connections to select one of them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting overlapping connections"
msgstr ""

#. type: #connections
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:97
msgid ""
"Connections automatically choose paths between their 2 ends. To customize "
"this path, select from 4 path modes by hovering over a connection and "
"pressing R. The bend modes of all connections on one component can be "
"changed by pressing R on the component."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "Path modes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network Selector"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network selector with no network"
msgstr ""

#. type: #network-selector
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:108
msgid ""
"Factory gauges need to be tuned to a network before being placed in the "
"controller. The first gauge needs to be tuned the usual way (e.g. by "
"interacting with a stock link with a gauge in hand). Once a tuned gauge is "
"placed in the controller, its network appears in the network selector."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:109
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network selector with a network selected"
msgstr ""

#. type: #network-selector
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:113
msgid ""
"With an empty cursor, scrolling with the mouse wheel selects one of the "
"tuned networks, highlighting all components tuned to that network with a "
"blue outline. The number of components tuned to the network also appears on "
"the network selector icon."
msgstr ""

#. type: #network-selector
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:115
msgid ""
"While holding a factory gauge item, scrolling on the network selector "
"changes the network this item is tuned to, allowing you to quickly tune a "
"new gauge to an existing network. Holding shift and scrolling accomplishes "
"the same."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "Warnings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "Additional Interactions"
msgstr ""

#. type: #additional-interactions
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:123
msgid ""
"Some components, like the xref:redstone-link.adoc[redstone link], have modes "
"of operation that can be switched either by pressing the F key while "
"hovering over them in the dashboard, or through their configuration UI."
msgstr ""

#. type: #additional-interactions
#: ../src/dashboard.adoc:125
msgid ""
"Each factory gauge displays a label, providing relevant information (e.g. "
"items in stock) at a glance. When the labels become distracting or obstruct "
"other components, they can be hidden by pressing Alt. Then only the label of "
"the hovered component is displayed. Press Alt again to show all labels."
msgstr ""

